                        s is a numerical semigroup.  The output is true if the numerical semigroup is telescopic in the sense of :
						it is either \mathbb N or the gluing of   \langle n_e\rangle and s'=\langle n_1/d,\ldots, n_{e-1}/d\rangle,
						and s' is again a telescopic numerical semigroup, where n_1 < \cdots < n_e  are the minimal generators of s.



                        This filter implies  and .

gap> IsTelescopic(NumericalSemigroup(4,11,14));
false
gap> IsTelescopicNumericalSemigroup(NumericalSemigroup(4,11,14));
false
gap> IsFree(NumericalSemigroup(4,11,14));
true







                        f is an integer. The output is the set of all
                        telescopic numerical semigroups with Frobenius number f.

gap> Length(TelescopicNumericalSemigroupsWithFrobeniusNumber(57));
20







                        s is a numerical semigroup.  The output is true if the numerical semigroup is associated to an irreducible planar curve singularity
